cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CE

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and analyzing classroom discussions. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes several methods and feature sets for predicting specificity. Additionally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the importance of high-quality classroom discussion for student development. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as classroom discussions involve social interactions between students. Finally, it could belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the proposed methods and features could be used to analyze classroom discussions at a pedagogical level.
